column5: Think I'll wait for Walleye opener...Dara...I get to "borrow" your HDS-7/SS till around....um...september right?
Great pic Doc...Almost looks like a water colour painting. Well done!  Awesome fish too TDunn!

At 4pm I finally decided to brave the cold and fish for a quick few hours... man it was cold! Frozen fingers, guides, and eventually a reel!  All things said, I did manage to get one fish, not bad considering I couldn't feel my fingers for the whole drive home!  Here's a quick cell phone pic.  TGIF EVERYBODY!  IT'S TIME FOR A BEVERAGE!
You're crazy. It was snowing sideways.  We need a few degrees to get me out there.  Good on ya though
I'm Finnish Dara. Which means that I eat icicles and whiz antifreeze!
you got ballz sal...i was out at the purvis scrap yard on the river yesterday helping my buddy drop some propane tanks off for them...thought i was going to turn into a block of ice
I can see why your reel eventually froze! Good job on the steel ! Iso kala
i agree, u got balls dude!! haha, but it payed off... thats actually a sweet picture, even for a cell phone, the colors on the fish and rocks just look great!
One of the best Steelhead pics I've seen in awhile. Kinda Avatar movie'esque'  Good on you for getting out!  Cheers!
a coffee with baileys and a few glasses of wine and no worse for wear... let's hope it warms up for sunday!
Right on dude, cold keeps the crowds away.  I started using an elastic to hold a handwarmer on the rod just at the reel.  Stuck in ottawa another night waiting for weather.....
Hardcore...I like it...Beauty steel man, great celly pic. Im suiting up heavily for a troll on the river this afternoon...   TDunn
oof...yup, she's be a little nipply out there... any luck?
Is the ice out of Goulais bay and Haviland yet?  I'm itching to troll for....ummm, whatevers out there
guys are still taking boats out to the ice on haviland.
Nothing crazy, 1/2... Lost one bouncing which I am assuming was a rainbow. Landed a 26" Atlantic trolling...Took a quick pic I'll add it in a bit. Tomorrow we have some serious plans tho...  TDunn
Beauty of a   fish buddy!
you mean boating out to fish on the ice or at the edge of it?
there's open water for the first 100 feet from shore.
I'm going to get out for an actual full day of steelheading tomorrow.  It's going to be cold but hopefully we can do some damage.
I'm hauling firewood away from my house and having an open house. Anybody want to buy a couple cords of maple?  Sal, its sposed to warm up nicely in the afternoon tomorrow
Dara, Get a hold of WormDangler, I believe he may be looking for some!
Early season St Marys Atlantic   TDunn
nice...I gotta get at it somehow

hmmmm, maybe i'll go for whities tomorrow... lord knows i need the exercise! lol.... built up a little belly from being stocked away for the winter. was a little cold out there for me this morning. hopefully no damn rain tomorrow though!  oh yea nice fish by the way TDunn!
beauty fish.
My god...blur the back ground we'll all know where you caught it!!!!!!!!!!
